  "texts": [
    "Despite this being the largest aligned set for our scenario at the time, the limited data size could hinder the generalizability of our attack strategies. 3.",
    "LoRA Fine-tuning.",
    "We employed LoRA to reduce computational overhead, enabling faster cycles of experimentation.",
    "Although effective for rapid iteration, LoRA may not capture the full nuances of traditional, largerscale fine-tuning protocols and thus could affect our attack's ultimate transferability. 4.",
    "Defense Considerations: We evaluated one representative defense (CLIP-based filtering) and proposed a more computationally expensive strategy reliant on a safety-aligned VLM to detect and remove malicious samples."
  ]
